-- Pacific Alliance Hires TPG Capital Partner Shan Weijian as Chairman, CEO
-- Cathy Chan
-- 2010-06-21T01:48:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/pacific-alliance-hires-tpg-capital-partner-shan-weijian-as-chairman-ceo.html

          
          
             Pacific Alliance Group , the Asia-
based alternative investment manager, appointed  Shan Weijian , a
partner at TPG Capital, as chairman and chief executive officer.  
 Shan, 56, will be responsible for a new Asia-focused
private-equity buyout fund for Pacific Alliance, the company
said in a statement today. His appointment is effective July 1.  
 Shan will maintain a business relationship with TPG, where
he has worked since 1998, Pacific Alliance said. Under the
arrangement, TPG will have certain rights to take part in co-
investment opportunities and Shan will continue to serve as an
adviser to a number of companies TPG invested in, it said.  
 Pacific Alliance and its affiliates manage about $5 billion
in private equity, real estate, hedge funds and distressed
investments, according to the release.  
 Pacific Alliance also hired  David Kim , the former head of
Asia financial institutions group at Nomura Holdings Inc., as a
partner and chief operating officer of the companyâ€™s private-
equity business, it said.  
